Metasoma in dorsal view elliptical (
Figure 1B
), about 1.44 times as long as wide, about 0.86 times as wide as mesoscutum, and as long as mesosoma (in natural, airdried specimens, metasoma severely collapsed with dorsum deeply sunken except for tergite 1, its width about 0.82 times length of mesoscutum and its length 1.58 times its width); cercus located at about basal third, with three long bristles; all tergites shiny without reticulation except last tergite with very dense, tiny punctures; tergites bare except basal tergite with three to four short setae laterally and with relatively dense setae behind spiracle; in lateral view apex of metasoma truncate (
Figure 1A
) with hypopygium extending to about same level as last tergite, and with triangular, densely setose ovipositor sheath exposed between them (
Figure 1A
); hypopygium ventrally with conspicuous setae, its posterior margin deeply excised medially, in ventral view appearing as a subcircular hollow (
Figure 2E
).
